<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-12T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1199a:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-13T00:00:00-04:00">December 13,
                                1943—midnight.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1365. Your 3908, December 2. Please inform the Foreign Minister that this
                        Government has read with much gratification the text of the <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> made to the German Minister at Stockholm on
                        the occasion of this further instance of barbaric and inhuman action by
                        Germany.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>